{"id":14881686,"mediaExerciseId":"72985e9e-07a9-409d-84a0-b23813406146","exerciseName":"9","chapterName":"19","chapterTitle":"Cash and Liquidity Management","groupId":612447,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":661,"solutions":[{"id":6394101,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will determine how much interest is added towards the payment of the company when they delay the transfer of funds for the loan.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"When managing cash in a firm, we must take note of the value of delay. This is essentially how much a certain delay can cost a company in terms of additional payments. When acquiring loans, it is important that a company makes timely payments in order to remove these cost of delays which can be huge when accumulated. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"In order to solve this, we must first recall the formula for solving the interest of payments with delay. The formula we will use is:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Interest}&=\\text{Principal amount} \\times \\text{Days delayed} \\times \\text{Rate for delay} \\times \\text{time}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nFor the time, we can see that the payment is done every two weeks, this means that there are $26$ payments done in a year. \n\nSubstituting the values, we will get:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Interest}&=\\$107,000 \\times 7\\ \\text{days} \\times 0.00009 \\times 26\\\\[15 pt]\n&=\\$1,752.66\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThere will be an interest of $\\$1,752.66$ for the delay. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"8b426a14-143d-4706-bdc7-e5b2a778595f","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881687,"exerciseName":"10","page":661,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"b40d253b-909e-4751-970f-3dd4930ee3a1","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-19-questions-and-problems-10-b40d253b-909e-4751-970f-3dd4930ee3a1"},{"id":14881688,"exerciseName":"11","page":661,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"a7d7bc01-3fa5-4c1f-81cc-9fc8955f4c94","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-19-questions-and-problems-11-a7d7bc01-3fa5-4c1f-81cc-9fc8955f4c94"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881685,"exerciseName":"8","page":661,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"9d185dbe-92d5-4eda-aa9a-f7a9db2c1dae","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-19-questions-and-problems-8-9d185dbe-92d5-4eda-aa9a-f7a9db2c1dae"},{"id":14881684,"exerciseName":"7","page":661,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"f5295624-a878-44cc-a91f-b21d63e8b5fd","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-19-questions-a